                  </hi>. I am a greengrocer, and live in Union-road, Clapham. Major Sheppard resides at Elm-house, Clapham-common—he has two-of three large gardens attached to his house—the prisoner was his gardener—I ever saw him before last July—I met his wife, and in consequence of wkat she said, I went down to Major Sheppard's cottage, where the gardener resides—I prisoner—he told me he had got fruit to sell in the garden, black currants, red currants, aud white currants, gooseberries, and</p>
