                  </hi>. I am in the service of Major Sheppard—I was at Clapham in June, when the family left—the prisoner was the gardener—I went with a letter to him on the 30th of June, when I received it—on the night the prisoner was taken he told the constable that he had paid the major 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 8<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 3<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., and that was all he had received.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">The letter contained the following sentence</hi>:—"Tell the gardener, and show him this letter, he had better dispose of the strawberries and currants, and vegetables; be can account to his master for them."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
