                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> I returned to town on the 20th of July—I sent the prisoner a verbal order on the 21st to discontinue selling any<lb></lb>thing—I did not see him for some days afterwards—about the 27th of July he paid me 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 8<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 3<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., and merely said that was the proceeds of the sale of the vegetables and fruit—I did not ask him any further questions.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184608170235"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> How did this man come into your service? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I wrote to Sir "William Jolliff for bis character—he bore a good character—honost, sober, and trustworthy—he lived with me exactly nine weeks—I have had nine gardeners within the last four years—the prisoner left me on the 1st of Aug.—there was no charge against him then.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Do you remember sending him away in consequence of a quarrel with the foot-boy, who was constantly bothering him to have the key? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> He was not sent away absolutely in consequence of that down several times for things, and he refused to open the gate I was forced to go down, and the prisoner said he did not choose to be called "gardener," and he did not choose to have so much plague and trouble, and J turtied him away—it was on the 1st of Aug.—I turned him out in the hall-strom—I bad the policeman there merely for the purpose of keeping the peace, the prisoner was making use of abusive language—when I gave him 'riotte to quit, he came up to me and said he thought he was coming in the ifemto of a gentleman, and I was a low blackguard; and his wife came out of the cottage and used the same words—when I gave him notice to quit, he round and said, "I will go on Saturday"—I said, "Of course in that case you will not have the week's wages."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PARRY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> You gave him notice to quit on the 29th? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, "and he on the Saturday—I believe the policeman did nothing towards oat, he only told him to go.</p>
